Core Thesis

SIMA proposes that AI systems should separate the representation used to store memories from the representation used to retrieve them, using compact category-indexed representations to identify relevant memories before progressively expanding full memory content into the active context.

The objective is not to make the context window physically larger.

The objective is to make the system's effective memory capacity substantially larger without proportionally increasing the amount of information that must be actively loaded into context.
