9. Relevance Ranking

A conceptual relevance function:

R(m,q) =
    w_s * S(m,q)
  + w_c * C(m,q)
  + w_t * T(m,q)
  + w_e * E(m,q)
  + w_i * I(m)

Where:

S = semantic similarity
C = category compatibility
T = temporal relevance
E = entity overlap
I = importance

The weights are tunable.

An implementation should expose these parameters for benchmarking.

