27. Final Architectural Thesis

SIMA proposes a fundamental separation:

Memory Storage
        !=
Memory Retrieval
        !=
Active Context

A memory can be:

Stored completely

while being:

Indexed compactly

and:

Retrieved selectively

and:

Expanded only when needed

The architecture therefore treats long-term memory as a persistent external information system rather than as a continuously active extension of the model's context.

The central research question is:

Can intelligent indexing and progressive expansion allow an AI system to operate over a memory corpus vastly larger than its active context window while preserving high-fidelity recall?

SIMA is an open-source attempt to answer that question experimentally.
